@Comment:	Time is 6:17
@Comment:	The mood surrounding the activity seems pleasant. Mot and Chi are friendly to each other , but spend much of their time playing independently. Mot does most of the talking. EXP remains in the background throughout the activity. Reference to the qualities of magnets is limited to comments by Mot that pennies will not stick to magnets. There is considerable experimentation with repulsion when Mot and Chi notice that different objects will move across the table because of the pressure of the magnets. Chi puts a washer underneath the plastic turtle's shell and is thus able to pick it up with the yellow wand. MOT and Chi sit at a table in the kitchen; the magnets are spread out on the table in front of them; Chi is stacking objects on the black base
